Basic Git commands learned in early days of using Git
- git init
- git status
- git log: view commits history
- git diff: view diff between files, commits
- git clone:
- git config --global color.ui auto: getting colored output in terminal
- git checkout: checkout a commit
- git config --global user.name "Your name": config user name
- git config --global user.email "youremail@domain.com": configure email
- git config --global core.editor, followed by the command you run to start your editor: configure default editor
- git add path/: add all file under path/ folder
